{"type":"message","id":"d7d8dccf","parentId":"62388bb7","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:55:56.655Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zd0lg4mszr0x_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5286\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=927\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\n\nProcess still running."}],"details":{"status":"running","sessionId":"mellow-trail","aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5286\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=927\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n[mutation proposed] tic/tic_classifier.ps1\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1","retryInMs":5000},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328156653}}
{"type":"message","id":"18ef4f63","parentId":"d7d8dccf","timestamp":"2026-03-24T04:55:56.657Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zd0lg4mszr0x_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 005314\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action to advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- There's been significant synthesis work on architecture comparison and gap-decay mapping\r\n- The next big action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment\r\n- Need to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nLooking at the pending actions:\r\n1. Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n2. Define `significance` scoring for pulse content\r\n3. Tune λ empirically (start: λ=0.7)\r\n4. Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n5. Measure compression ratio: original vs. summarized pulse\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step that would advance the unified Phase 1/Phase 2 goal is the TIC Experiment. But implementing a full TIC classifier is a larger task.\r\n\r\nLet me look for something specific and actionable. The notes mention pulse_2026-03-24 005115.md as the last pulse. Let me check what files exist and what would be a good concrete action.\r\n\r\nGiven the \"compression-causal duality\" insight and the TIC experiment as the next step, I should:\r\n1. Look at existing pulse logs\r\n2. Start implementing a simple TIC classifier or\r\n3. Work on one of the smaller pending tasks like significance scoring\r\n\r\nLet me check the current directory structure and recent files to find a concrete, actionable edit.\r\n\r\nLooking at the state, I should create a file that advances the TIC experiment. A good concrete action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier, perhaps by creating a Python script that can analyze pulse logs for invariants.\r\n\r\nLet me write a Python script that implements the basic TIC classifier logic - analyzing pulse logs to find invariant vs variant patterns.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment requires a working classifier. The pulse logs exist but no implementation tool is present to analyze them for invariants. A Python classifier script is the most direct way to begin testing the compression-causal duality hypothesis.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `tic/tic_classifier.py` - a Python script that loads recent pulse logs, extracts features, and classifies content as invariant or variant. This is the foundational tool needed before measuring accuracy against the >70% success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\nTests hypothesis: causal structure IS invariant structure\r\nSuccess criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n                 >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\n\r\nLOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMIN_LOGS = 5\r\n\r\ndef extract_pulse_features(pulse_path):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structural features from a pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_path.read_text()\r\n    \r\n    # Extract key sections\r\n    obs_match = re.search(r'### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    action_match = re.search(r'### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)', content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    \r\n    obs_text = obs_match.group(1).strip() if obs_match else \"\"\r\n    action_text = action_match.group(1).strip() if action_match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        'path': str(pulse_path),\r\n        'observation': obs_text,\r\n        'action': action_text,\r\n        'obs_len': len(obs_text.split()),\r\n        'action_len': len(action_text.split()),\r\n        'full_text': content\r\n    }\r\n\r\ndef load_pulse_logs(n=20):\r\n    \"\"\"Load the n most recent pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    logs = sorted(LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)\r\n    return [extract_pulse_features(p) for p in logs[:n]]\r\n\r\ndef compute_invariant_features(pulses):\r\n    \"\"\"Compute invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant features.\"\"\"\r\n    all_obs = [p['observation'] for p in pulses]\r\n    all_actions = [p['action'] for p in pulses]\r\n    \r\n    # Invariant = appears in multiple pulses\r\n    obs_words = Counter(w for obs in all_obs for w in obs.lower().split())\r\n    action_words = Counter(w for act in all_actions for w in act.lower().split())\r\n    \r\n    # Words appearing in >60% of pulses = invariant\r\n    threshold = len(pulses) * 0.6\r\n    inv_obs = {w for w, c in obs_words.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    inv_actions = {w for w, c in action_words.items() if c >= threshold}\r\n    \r\n    return inv_obs, inv_actions\r\n\r\ndef classify_pulse(pulse, inv_obs, inv_actions):\r\n    \"\"\"Classify a pulse as invariant-heavy or variant-heavy.\"\"\"\r\n    obs_words = set(pulse['observation'].lower().split())\r\n    act_words = set(pulse['action'].lower().split())\r\n    \r\n    inv_count = len(obs_words & inv_obs) + len(act_words & inv_actions)\r\n    total = len(obs_words) + len(act_words)\r\n    \r\n    ratio = inv_count / total if total > 0 else 0\r\n    return 'INVARIANT' if ratio > 0.4 else 'VARIANT', ratio\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(curr_pulse, next_pulse, inv_obs, inv_actions):\r\n    \"\"\"Test if invariants in current predict next pulse structure.\"\"\"\r\n    curr_inv = set(curr_pulse['observation'].lower().split()) & inv_obs\r\n    # Simplified: predict if next has similar invariant ratio\r\n    _, ratio = classify_pulse(next_pulse, inv_obs, inv_actions)\r\n    return ratio > 0.3  #\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 00:53:38\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774328156655}}
